{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_40","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Resume semantics after remediation-commit failure**: a failed `cycle_advanced` append can leave a run resumable from the wrong stage.\nCurrent: the remediation path persists the next-cycle cursor before appending `cycle_advanced` in [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L599), [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L614), and [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L639). If that append fails, the run is marked failed, but resume reconstruction only consults durable `stage_completed` and `cycle_advanced` events in [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L1366) and [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L1371). That means a QA `request_changes` payload can resume at the next sequential stage instead of looping back to `implementation`.\nExpected: a remediation handoff failure must still resume deterministically at `implementation` for the incremented cycle, or fail fast as non-resumable until a durable remediation marker exists. `run resume` must not skip the required remediation loop after `request_changes`.\nReference: acceptance criteria for QA/Review `RequestChanges`, `run resume`, and the failure-state invariant.\n\n2. **Conformance coverage and scenario updates**: the public behavior added in this loop is not reflected in Gherkin, and one existing scenario now contradicts the new paused invariant.\nCurrent: there are no `run resume`, retry, remediation, or prompt-review pause scenarios anywhere under [tests/conformance/features](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features); the flow coverage is still only the straight-through `run start` suite in [run_start_standard.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature#L1). Also, [run_queries.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_queries.feature#L131) still says `paused` with `active_run null` is inconsistent, while the model now defines that as the valid paused state in [model.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs#L66) and [model.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs#L83).\nExpected: add or update scenario IDs covering `run resume`, retry exhaustion/success, QA remediation, prompt-review pause, and `run start` rejection for `failed`/`paused`; also fix the paused-state scenario to match the canonical snapshot invariant.\nReference: master prompt section 15 “Testability Requirements” and the acceptance criteria for resume/retry/pause behavior.\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. The `ValidatedBundle` docs in [contracts.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs#L48) still say non-passing QA/review outcomes never return a bundle, which is no longer true after `evaluate_permissive()`. Updating that comment would prevent future confusion."}}
