{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_39","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc 'nl -ba /root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_resume_retry.feature'","aggregated_output":"     1\tFeature: Retry, Remediation, and Resume\n     2\t  Standard-flow runs retry retryable stage failures, pause for prompt-review\n     3\t  revision, loop through remediation cycles when QA or review request\n     4\t  changes, and resume only from durable stage boundaries.\n     5\t\n     6\t  # SC-RESUME-001\n     7\t  Scenario: Retryable implementation failure succeeds on the second attempt\n     8\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n     9\t    And project \"alpha\" is selected as active\n    10\t    And the implementation stage will fail once with a transport failure\n    11\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    12\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    13\t    And the journal contains a \"stage_failed\" event for \"implementation\" with attempt 1 and will_retry true\n    14\t    And the journal contains a second \"stage_entered\" event for \"implementation\" with attempt 2\n    15\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n    16\t\n    17\t  # SC-RESUME-002\n    18\t  Scenario: Retry exhaustion fails the run and clears the active cursor\n    19\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"bravo\" using flow \"standard\"\n    20\t    And project \"bravo\" is selected as active\n    21\t    And the implementation stage will fail for all retry attempts with a transport failure\n    22\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    23\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"implementation\"\n    24\t    And the journal ends with a \"run_failed\" event referencing \"implementation\"\n    25\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\" with no active run\n    26\t\n    27\t  # SC-RESUME-003\n    28\t  Scenario: QA request_changes advances the cycle and reruns implementation\n    29\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"charlie\" using flow \"standard\"\n    30\t    And project \"charlie\" is selected as active\n    31\t    And the QA stage returns \"request_changes\" with follow-up amendment \"add missing regression test\"\n    32\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    33\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    34\t    And the journal contains a \"cycle_advanced\" event from cycle 1 to cycle 2 resuming at \"implementation\"\n    35\t    And the implementation stage is entered twice across the run\n    36\t    And the second implementation invocation includes the QA follow-up amendment in its remediation context\n    37\t\n    38\t  # SC-RESUME-004\n    39\t  Scenario: Prompt review not ready pauses the run for revision\n    40\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"delta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    41\t    And project \"delta\" is selected as active\n    42\t    And the prompt_review stage returns readiness.ready false\n    43\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    44\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    45\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"paused\" with no active run\n    46\t    And the status summary instructs the user to revise the prompt and run \"run resume\"\n    47\t    And the prompt_review payload and artifact are persisted before the pause\n    48\t\n    49\t  # SC-RESUME-005\n    50\t  Scenario: Run resume continues a failed run from the first incomplete durable stage\n    51\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"echo\" using flow \"standard\"\n    52\t    And project \"echo\" is selected as active\n    53\t    And a previous \"run start\" failed after planning completed and implementation exhausted retries\n    54\t    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n    55\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    56\t    And the resumed run keeps the original run_id\n    57\t    And the planning stage is not re-executed\n    58\t    And the first resumed stage is \"implementation\" with attempt 1\n    59\t\n    60\t  # SC-RESUME-006\n    61\t  Scenario: Run resume continues a paused prompt-review run from planning\n    62\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"foxtrot\" using flow \"standard\"\n    63\t    And project \"foxtrot\" is selected as active\n    64\t    And a previous \"run start\" paused after \"prompt_review\" with readiness.ready false\n    65\t    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n    66\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    67\t    And the resumed run keeps the original run_id\n    68\t    And the first resumed stage is \"planning\" with attempt 1\n    69\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n    70\t\n    71\t  # SC-RESUME-007\n    72\t  Scenario: Run resume rejects non-resumable snapshot statuses\n    73\t    Given initialized workspace projects with standard-flow snapshots in statuses \"not_started\", \"running\", and \"completed\"\n    74\t    When the user runs \"run resume\" for each project\n    75\t    Then each command fails with a clear status-specific error\n    76\t    And none of the commands mutate canonical run state\n    77\t\n    78\t  # SC-RESUME-008\n    79\t  Scenario: Run start rejects failed or paused snapshots and directs the user to resume\n    80\t    Given initialized workspace projects with standard-flow snapshots in statuses \"failed\" and \"paused\"\n    81\t    When the user runs \"run start\" for each project\n    82\t    Then each command fails with error containing \"run resume\"\n    83\t    And no new run_id is created for either project\n    84\t\n    85\t  # SC-RESUME-009\n    86\t  Scenario: Cancellation during a retry loop halts further retries immediately\n    87\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"golf\" using flow \"standard\"\n    88\t    And project \"golf\" is selected as active\n    89\t    And the implementation stage is cancelled during its first retryable failure\n    90\t    When the engine handles the failure\n    91\t    Then no further \"stage_entered\" events are emitted for \"implementation\"\n    92\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\" with no active run\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_40","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba /root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs | sed -n '70,220p'\"","aggregated_output":"    70\t    AgentExecutionService::new(adapter, FsRawOutputStore, FsSessionStore)\n    71\t}\n    72\t\n    73\tasync fn handle_start() -> AppResult<()> {\n    74\t    let current_dir = std::env::current_dir()?;\n    75\t\n    76\t    // Validate workspace version\n    77\t    let config = workspace_governance::load_workspace_config(&current_dir)?;\n    78\t    workspace_governance::ensure_supported_workspace_version(&config)?;\n    79\t\n    80\t    // Resolve active project\n    81\t    let project_id = workspace_governance::resolve_active_project(&current_dir)?;\n    82\t\n    83\t    // Validate canonical project record\n    84\t    let project_store = FsProjectStore;\n    85\t    let project_record = project_store.read_project_record(&current_dir, &project_id)?;\n    86\t\n    87\t    // Only standard flow is supported in this slice\n    88\t    if project_record.flow != FlowPreset::Standard {\n    89\t        return Err(AppError::UnsupportedFlow {\n    90\t            flow_id: project_record.flow.as_str().to_owned(),\n    91\t        });\n    92\t    }\n    93\t\n    94\t    // Validate run snapshot integrity\n    95\t    let run_snapshot_read = FsRunSnapshotStore;\n    96\t    let run_snapshot = run_snapshot_read.read_run_snapshot(&current_dir, &project_id)?;\n    97\t\n    98\t    // Check preconditions before engine call (fail fast with clear errors)\n    99\t    match run_snapshot.status {\n   100\t        RunStatus::NotStarted => {}\n   101\t        RunStatus::Failed | RunStatus::Paused => {\n   102\t            return Err(AppError::RunStartFailed {\n   103\t                reason: format!(\n   104\t                    \"project snapshot status is '{}'; use `ralph-burning run resume`\",\n   105\t                    run_snapshot.status\n   106\t                ),\n   107\t            });\n   108\t        }\n   109\t        status => {\n   110\t            return Err(AppError::RunStartFailed {\n   111\t                reason: format!(\n   112\t                    \"project snapshot status is '{}'; run start requires 'not_started'\",\n   113\t                    status\n   114\t                ),\n   115\t            });\n   116\t        }\n   117\t    }\n   118\t    if run_snapshot.has_active_run() {\n   119\t        return Err(AppError::RunStartFailed {\n   120\t            reason: \"project already has an active run\".to_owned(),\n   121\t        });\n   122\t    }\n   123\t\n   124\t    let effective_config = EffectiveConfig::load(&current_dir)?;\n   125\t\n   126\t    let agent_service = build_agent_execution_service();\n   127\t    let run_snapshot_write = FsRunSnapshotWriteStore;\n   128\t    let journal_store = FsJournalStore;\n   129\t    let artifact_write = FsPayloadArtifactWriteStore;\n   130\t    let log_write = FsRuntimeLogWriteStore;\n   131\t\n   132\t    println!(\"Starting run for project '{}'...\", project_id);\n   133\t\n   134\t    engine::execute_standard_run(\n   135\t        &agent_service,\n   136\t        &run_snapshot_read,\n   137\t        &run_snapshot_write,\n   138\t        &journal_store,\n   139\t        &artifact_write,\n   140\t        &log_write,\n   141\t        &current_dir,\n   142\t        &project_id,\n   143\t        &effective_config,\n   144\t    )\n   145\t    .await?;\n   146\t\n   147\t    let final_snapshot = run_snapshot_read.read_run_snapshot(&current_dir, &project_id)?;\n   148\t    match final_snapshot.status {\n   149\t        RunStatus::Completed => println!(\"Run completed successfully.\"),\n   150\t        RunStatus::Paused => println!(\"{}\", final_snapshot.status_summary),\n   151\t        status => println!(\"Run finished with status '{}'.\", status),\n   152\t    }\n   153\t    Ok(())\n   154\t}\n   155\t\n   156\tasync fn handle_resume() -> AppResult<()> {\n   157\t    let current_dir = std::env::current_dir()?;\n   158\t\n   159\t    let config = workspace_governance::load_workspace_config(&current_dir)?;\n   160\t    workspace_governance::ensure_supported_workspace_version(&config)?;\n   161\t\n   162\t    let project_id = workspace_governance::resolve_active_project(&current_dir)?;\n   163\t\n   164\t    let project_store = FsProjectStore;\n   165\t    let project_record = project_store.read_project_record(&current_dir, &project_id)?;\n   166\t    if project_record.flow != FlowPreset::Standard {\n   167\t        return Err(AppError::UnsupportedFlow {\n   168\t            flow_id: project_record.flow.as_str().to_owned(),\n   169\t        });\n   170\t    }\n   171\t\n   172\t    let run_snapshot_read = FsRunSnapshotStore;\n   173\t    let run_snapshot = run_snapshot_read.read_run_snapshot(&current_dir, &project_id)?;\n   174\t    match run_snapshot.status {\n   175\t        RunStatus::Failed | RunStatus::Paused => {}\n   176\t        RunStatus::NotStarted => {\n   177\t            return Err(AppError::ResumeFailed {\n   178\t                reason: \"project has not started a run yet; use `ralph-burning run start`\"\n   179\t                    .to_owned(),\n   180\t            });\n   181\t        }\n   182\t        RunStatus::Running => {\n   183\t            return Err(AppError::ResumeFailed {\n   184\t                reason: \"project already has a running run; `run resume` only works from failed or paused snapshots\".to_owned(),\n   185\t            });\n   186\t        }\n   187\t        RunStatus::Completed => {\n   188\t            return Err(AppError::ResumeFailed {\n   189\t                reason: \"project is already completed; there is nothing to resume\".to_owned(),\n   190\t            });\n   191\t        }\n   192\t    }\n   193\t    if run_snapshot.has_active_run() {\n   194\t        return Err(AppError::ResumeFailed {\n   195\t            reason: \"failed or paused snapshots must not retain an active run\".to_owned(),\n   196\t        });\n   197\t    }\n   198\t\n   199\t    let effective_config = EffectiveConfig::load(&current_dir)?;\n   200\t    let agent_service = build_agent_execution_service();\n   201\t    let run_snapshot_write = FsRunSnapshotWriteStore;\n   202\t    let journal_store = FsJournalStore;\n   203\t    let artifact_write = FsPayloadArtifactWriteStore;\n   204\t    let log_write = FsRuntimeLogWriteStore;\n   205\t\n   206\t    println!(\"Resuming run for project '{}'...\", project_id);\n   207\t\n   208\t    engine::resume_standard_run(\n   209\t        &agent_service,\n   210\t        &run_snapshot_read,\n   211\t        &run_snapshot_write,\n   212\t        &journal_store,\n   213\t        &FsArtifactStore,\n   214\t        &artifact_write,\n   215\t        &log_write,\n   216\t        &current_dir,\n   217\t        &project_id,\n   218\t        &effective_config,\n   219\t    )\n   220\t    .await?;\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
