{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_48","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Retry-loop cancellation boundary**: cancellation can still start one extra retry attempt if the token flips after the engine decides to retry and before the next attempt begins.\n   - Current: [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L948) computes `will_retry` once from the current token state, but the next loop iteration immediately emits `stage_entered` and rewrites the running snapshot at [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L812) without a fresh cancellation check. That leaves a race where a late cancellation still records attempt `N+1`, so the retry loop has not halted immediately.\n   - Expected: Re-check `cancellation_token` before emitting `StageEntered` or mutating `run.json` for the next retry attempt, and terminate as `Cancellation` without starting another attempt. Add regression coverage for cancellation arriving after the retry decision but before the next attempt starts.\n   - Reference: Loop 7 acceptance criterion: \"Cancellation signal during a retry loop immediately halts all further retries for that stage.\"\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. The rest of loop 7 looks aligned and `nix develop -c cargo test` passed; after fixing the guard above, strengthen [workflow_engine_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs#L1659) so it covers the between-attempt cancellation window, not just cancellation during the first failing attempt."}}
